column1: # Data from Charles Creighton. A History of Epidemics in Britain. Frank Cass & Co. Ltd. 1965. p. 436
# All cause mortality is not available in Creighton from 1637-1660 & 1838-1893.

# 1837 has two different values for smallpox deaths. The data Creighton pulls from the London Bills of Mortality gives 217 as the total  while another source he uses gives 763 as the total number of smallpox deaths. He mentions an epidemic that year so the higher value is likely the more accurate of the two.
